<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF49624879CCFD2C" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4962487BFEFD64" bold="true" box="[199,467,620,645]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E479FFC3FC9B624879A0FD64" authorityName="Pinho &amp; Mendes &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="2013" box="[789,909,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tupinamba">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FC9B624879A0FD64" box="[789,909,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">tupinamba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="948C4D30E479FFC3FECE62AB7B95FD49" authorityName="Pinho &amp; Mendes &amp; Andersen" authorityYear="2013" box="[320,440,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tupinamba">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FECE62AB7B95FD49" box="[320,440,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">tupinamba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the combination of the following characters: large body size (
<quantity id="94749B56E479FFC3FB7162AB7FA2FD49" box="[1279,1423,655,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="4.35" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="3.8">3.8–4.9 mm</quantity>
); coloration brown; R 
<subScript id="CF0834F6E479FFC3FEF662E77BADFD30" attach="left" box="[376,384,707,721]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">1</subScript>
with setae; and superior volsella without microtrichia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1B966538E479FFCCFF4962FE7873F851" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF4962FE7ED7FD12" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" box="[199,1274,730,755]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4962FE7B63FD12" bold="true" box="[199,334,730,755]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Dr. Luís Eduardo Maestrelli Bizzo for collecting some of the material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF1962DA7B37FCF6" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" box="[151,282,766,791]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF4963067ECBFCBE" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4963067B29FCDA" bold="true" box="[199,260,802,827]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Male</emphasis>
(n = 8–9, except when otherwise stated). Total length 3.81–4.90, 
<quantity id="94749B56E479FFC3FC6663067E62FCDB" box="[1000,1103,802,827]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.43" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="4.43">4.43 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 2.26–2.68, 
<quantity id="94749B56E479FFC3FAE563067AEBFCBF" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.51" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="2.51">2.51 mm</quantity>
. Total length / wing length 1.68–1.88, 1.77. Wing length / length of profemur 2.24–2.54, 2.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF49634E7BD4FC46" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF49634E7B64FC62" box="[199,329,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head and abdomen light brown. Thorax pale with scutum, vittae, postnotum and preepisternum stramineous. Legs stramineous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF4963967AD1FBBA" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4963967B26FC2A" box="[199,267,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.04–1.28, 1.16; ultimate flagellomere 594–749, 696 µm long. Temporal setae 10–13, 11; not well separated in inner and outer verticals and postorbitals. Clypeus with 15–18, 16 setae. Tentorium 134–195, 152 µm long; 30–51, 40 µm wide. Stipes 159–202, 182 (6) µm long. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 35–48, 43; 43–51, 48; 172–202, 190; 175–202, 190; 240–311, 276. Third palpomere with 5–6, 5 sensillae subapically, longest 20–28, 23 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF496442787DFB43" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4964427B32FB9E" box="[199,287,1126,1151]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Thorax.</emphasis>
Scutal tubercle absent. Antepronotum without setae. Dorsocentrals 7–10, 9; acrostichals absent; prealars 2. Scutellum with 4–6, 5 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="533336B3E479FFC3FF4964947902FB0F" blockId="23.[151,1436,511,1370]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="61F8EAA1E479FFC3FF4964947B2CFB26" box="[199,257,1200,1223]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Wing</emphasis>
(
